This paper focuses on natural language processing tasks using deep learning-based language models, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper specifically evaluates the performance of multilingual BERT models on Finnish language tasks, which relates to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces a new Finnish BERT model trained from scratch, which could be relevant to neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
